The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, March 31: Moser Baer India has acquired a 40 per cent equity stake in Slovenia-based Solarvalue Proizvodnja from Germany-based Solarvalue ag for an undisclosed amount. The move will give it an assured supply of solar grade silicon for its photo voltaic business. Moser Baer Indias wholly owned subsidiary, Moser Baer Photo Voltaic (mbpv), acquired the strategic stake from Solarvalue, which owns the Slovenian firm.

 New Delhi, March 31: The phasing out of central sales tax (CST) will begin from tomorrow, although a year after and in a diluted form than was envisaged originally. Cst will be cut from 4 per cent to 3 per cent as part of its elimination by 2010-11. The new rate will pave the way for a cut in taxes on various commodities bought through inter-state trade, said a senior official of the finance ministry.

 Calcutta, March 31: The Damodar Valley Corporation (DVC) has said the fifth unit of the Mejia thermal power plant will be ready to generate 250 mw from June this year. The fifth unit of Mejia has been successfully synchronised on March 30. This is the only generation unit in the eastern region synchronised in the 10th plan period, a company statement said.

 Mumbai, March 31: Forex reserves increased by $1.789 billion to $197.746 billion during the week ended March 23 against $195.957 billion during the seven-day period ended on March 16. The reserves had increased by $1.55 billion during the week ended March 16 compared with the preceding week.

 New Delhi, March 31: The Aditya Birla group will invest $260 million (about Rs 1,170 crore) in its viscose staple fibre (vsf) business to set up a greenfield facility and increase the production capacity. The company will increase the capacity to 727 kilo tonnes per annum (ktpa) from 566 ktpa. It will also set up a greenfield plant to cater to the vsf demand in West Asia and the Latin American markets.




